<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-16T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-16T13:36:00-05:00" n="548" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">125.61383/175: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-16T12:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">November
                                            16, 1919, noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 7.26 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>3277. Jenkins telegraphs that he was released without bail after two
                                hours detention in penitentiary and is now restricted to his home.
                                In a signed statement published in local press today prosecuting
                                attorney [of] Puebla says Jenkins is guilty of criminal
                                responsibility and giving false evidence and has been transferred to
                                his home to avoid recurrence of recent illness.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>